3. Basic Structure of a C Program
THEORY EXERCISE

Basic structure includes:

Header files
Example: #include<stdio.h>
Main function
Entry point of program
Comments
// single line
/* multi-line */
Variables and Data Types
int, float, char

Example:

#include<stdio.h>

// main function
int main() {
    int a = 10;
    float b = 5.5;
    char c = 'A';

    printf("%d %f %c", a, b, c);
    return 0;
}
